1 (i) Six (6) members of the senate appointed by
2 the president to include one (1) member from the senate
3 minority political party;
4
5 (ii) Six (6) members of the house of
6 representatives appointed by the speaker to include one (1)
7 member from the house minority political party.
8
9 (b) The president of the senate and the speaker of
10 the house of representatives shall each select one (1)
11 co-chairman of the select committee. The legislative
12 service office shall staff the select committee.
13
14 (c) The select committee shall undertake a study to
15 recalibrate the education resource block grant model as
16 required by W.S. 21-13-309(t) to determine if modifications
17 are necessary to ensure the model remains cost-based in
18 light of changing conditions, including modifications to
19 law and potential responses to court directives. The select
20 committee shall study virtual education funding models in
21 other states and offer suggestions on a funding formula for
22 Wyoming virtual schools that is both equitable and
23 predictable. Further, the select committee shall study
