1 charter school funding models in other states and offer
2 suggestions on a funding formula for charter schools that
3 is both equitable and predictable. The select committee may
4 work with professional consultant experts for model
5 recalibration. The legislative service office, subject to
6 the approval of management council, may retain professional
7 consulting experts for the purposes of this act.
8
9 (d) The select committee shall report its
10 recommendations and any associated legislation to the
11 legislature. The select committee may introduce legislation
12 as provided in W.S. 28-8-104(e).
13
14 (e) Appointments to the select committee shall be
15 made under this section not later than March 31, 2025. The
16 select committee shall remain in existence until February
17 9, 2026. Any vacancy occurring on the select committee
18 shall be filled without delay by the president of the
19 senate or the speaker of the house, as appropriate.
20
21 (f) The department of education, other state
22 agencies, school districts and the school data advisory
23 committee established under W.S. 21-2-203(d) shall collect
